4 (9), 195. (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 41–44" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1531,1556]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,832,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[243,1344,832,1481]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 41–44. 41. Genus Coscinia: Coscinia cribraria, carterpillar; 42. Genus Sagarriella gen. nov.: Sagarriella romei, carterpillar; 43. Genus Spiris: Spiris striata, carterpillar; 44. Genus Lerautia stat. rev.: Lerautia bifasciata, carterpillar." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246072/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,898,2041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Several morphological features have been found which show the taxa, hitherto known as 
<taxonomicName box="[1164,1275,898,925]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[1164,1275,898,925]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">C. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[1331,1429,899,925]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[1331,1429,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">C. romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, form a monophyletic group, which is sister to another monophyletic group that includes the 
<typeStatus box="[1173,1221,935,961]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribraria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">C. cribraria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on these findings, we propose the new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Macia, Mally, Ylla, Gaston &amp; Huertas" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[766,1325,970,997]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[766,894,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
Macià, Mally, Ylla, Gastón &amp; Huertas
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1332,1436,970,996]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1332,1436,970,996]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
for the taxa 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[286,350,1007,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[286,350,1007,1032]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[404,482,1006,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[404,482,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[553,724,1007,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[553,724,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[761,809,1007,1033]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="420" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,898,2041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1041,1068]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[482,610,1042,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[482,610,1042,1068]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[843,943,1043,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[843,943,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure and geometry of the valvae. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[183,311,1078,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[183,311,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, these are elongated with parallel edges, and the apex (cucullus) consists of two sharp, closely associated processes, reminiscent of a crab’s claws (
<figureCitation box="[716,814,1114,1140]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40a</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus is cylindrical as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1209,1309,1115,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1209,1309,1115,1141]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1325,1424,1114,1141]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40b</figureCitation>
), but differs in the coecum penis, which is not globular but rather slightly pointed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[1112,1240,1150,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1112,1240,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1257,1345,1150,1177]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
b’). Furthermore, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[297,425,1186,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[297,425,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the aedeagus has a dense group of highly sclerotized cornuti in the distal zone (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1428,1186,1212]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40c</figureCitation>
) which is absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[358,458,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,458,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[472,557,1222,1248]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
c’), being replaced by a dense spot of spinules and a sclerotized plate, except in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Exposito" authorityYear="1991" box="[151,312,1259,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariarosae">
<emphasis box="[151,312,1259,1285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">C. mariarosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which certainly has a few cornuti in the central part, accompanied by the typical sclerotized plaque of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[182,282,1295,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,282,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[451,579,1294,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[451,579,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the bursa (
<figureCitation box="[711,794,1294,1321]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
d’) lacks the characteristic sclerotic belt of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1276,1376,1295,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1376,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40d</figureCitation>
), which makes it adopt a bilobal form, and the cervix bursae in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[918,1046,1330,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[918,1046,1330,1356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1062,1156,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40e</figureCitation>
) is much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,251,1367,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,251,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[266,351,1366,1392]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
e’).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,898,2041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,327,1402,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,327,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[625,690,1403,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,690,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of the clavus at the base of the valvae, which is characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[289,354,1439,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,354,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[370,465,1438,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40f</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, the uncus is short, wide and apically shovel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1321,1438,1464]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1277,1321,1438,1464]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" unit="g" value="40.0">40g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1364,1429,1439,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1364,1429,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[282,410,1474,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[282,410,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is narrow, slender and apically pointed (
<figureCitation box="[897,997,1474,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40h</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1050,1115,1475,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1115,1475,1501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the aedeagus has a bulging central part (
<figureCitation box="[294,385,1510,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40j</figureCitation>
) but in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[473,601,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[473,601,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is evenly cylindrical (
<figureCitation box="[875,968,1510,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Fig. 
<date box="[928,968,1510,1537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" value="1940-01">40i</date>
</figureCitation>
). In the females, the main difference is in the large, sclerotized lamella antevaginalis present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[758,823,1547,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[758,823,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[840,940,1546,1573]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40k</figureCitation>
), which is small and more inconspicuous in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,279,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[294,386,1582,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40l</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,898,2041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
The males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[350,478,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[350,478,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[707,803,1619,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[707,803,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the narrow, elongated uncus (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1262,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40h</figureCitation>
), which is thick and broad in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[295,391,1655,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,391,1655,1680]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[406,512,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[457,512,1654,1680]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" unit="m" value="40.0">40m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). The valvae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[687,815,1654,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[687,815,1654,1680]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much more slender, especially distally, as compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[181,277,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,277,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which there is a process located on the distal costa (
<figureCitation box="[913,1013,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40n</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[1225,1321,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1321,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not cylindrical (
<figureCitation box="[261,358,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40o</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[434,562,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[434,562,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but more funnel-shaped, with a characteristic swelling in the posterior third. In females, 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[282,410,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[282,410,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[557,653,1763,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[557,653,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the cup-shaped antrum (
<figureCitation box="[959,1057,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40q</figureCitation>
), which is wide and sclerotized in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[151,247,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,247,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[262,360,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40p</figureCitation>
). The ductus bursae is very broad and membranous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[961,1057,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1057,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1072,1164,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40r</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[1309,1437,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1309,1437,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is thin and partially sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[539,634,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40s</figureCitation>
). The cervix bursae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kemal &amp; Kocak" authorityYear="2006" box="[895,991,1835,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lerautia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[895,991,1835,1860]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Lerautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is voluminous and partially sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[160,252,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[212,252,1870,1896]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" unit="t" value="40.0">40t</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), unlike 
<taxonomicName authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[348,476,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[348,476,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which it is thinner and longer (
<figureCitation box="[856,953,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,242,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[227,1360,240,1717]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 40. Diagnosis genus Sagarriella gen. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Fig. 40e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="421" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,898,2041]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,153,647]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="421" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,439,1905,1932]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Description. Imago.</emphasis>
Small or medium size, head and thorax small, covered with scales, eyes large, palps short, proboscis of male short and functional; antenna of male bipectinate, thin and moderately long; that of female filiform. Foreleg tibia with a short spur. Forewings long, narrow and apically pointed, with a more or less marked golden orange ochre suffusion. Hindwings wide, tip acute, termen slightly concave towards tip; brown ochre in colour, submarginal zone with a fine golden orange tint. Females usually of smaller wingspan, with narrower, apically more pointed wings and paler colour. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[641,819,188,215]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Uncus tubular and lanceolate, with pointed tip; valvae rectangular, with a pointed apical cucullus and a subapical triangular process, giving the tip of the valva the appearance of a “crab claw”. Aedeagus cylindrical with a coecum slightly pointed, posterior end with a large number of small thorn-like cornuti. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[432,637,296,323]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Great disproportion of the ninth and eighth abdominal segments when compared to the rest of the genital structure, especially the bursa, which is considerably minor; ductus bursae short, strongly esclerotized; bursa membraneous (
<tableCitation box="[638,721,369,395]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1126,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Overview of compared genitalia features in the investigated genera." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3C8EEAA19F2A1C31FF50647B7EAC3A02" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" tableUuid="3C8EEAA19F2A1C31FF50647B7EAC3A02">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="421" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,404,431]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Derivatio nominis.</emphasis>
We dedicate the genus to the eminent entomologist Ignasi de Sagarra, the former curator of the Museum of Natural Sciences of Barcelona (MCNB) and author of the 
<typeStatus box="[980,1028,441,467]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">type</typeStatus>
species of the new genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,153,647]" box="[199,374,476,503]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,476,503]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Taxa included.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
